    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Added rigid barrier around pin end of tubing joints with red hazard tape",
      "Added trough over grating from pipe rack to rigid barrier",
      "Added Safe Zone requirement to JSA for future operations",
      "Repositioned out of service crane boom to eliminate blind lifts"
    ],
    "summary": "On 17-OCT-2016 at 0100 hours, an injured person was struck in the chest by a 30-foot tubing joint weighing 13.3 ppf during a blind lift operation at West Cameron 180G platform. The box end of the joint contacted the tong arm, causing the pin end to rise and strike the IP in the chest. The IP fell and the joint landed on his ankle, fracturing it and requiring evacuation.",
